About the university

~ $16,000 / year
Care for international students Participation in scientific research Modern campus

The New Jersey Institute of Technology (NJIT) is a public research university in the University Heights neighborhood of Newark, New Jersey. NJIT is New Jersey's Science & Technology University. Centrally located in the New York metropolitan area its campus is within walking distance of downtown Newark. New York City, 9 miles (14.5 km) and under 30 minutes away, is directly accessible from campus via public transit

How to apply to the university

  1. Choose a program

  2. Press “Apply now” button

  3. Send an admissions form

  4. Complete admissions tasks

  5. Go to study

To apply to New Jersey Institute of Technology follow these steps. To get more information about the university and the admissions process, you can use the live chat to contact a university representative.

Required documents for admission

When applying for admission to New Jersey Institute of Technology in United States you should prepare all required documents. Request a list of necessary documents directly from a university, as it may vary for different countries. Using our live chat, you can also ask for sample documents.

  • Photographs
  • Family Details
  • Student visa
  • Health and Life Insurance
  • Letters of reccomendation (MA, PhD)
  • Letters of reccomendation (for undergraduate)
  • Passport
  • Online Application form
  • World Education Services evaluation
  • Application fee
  • Proof of fee payment
  • TOEFL Certificate
  • Declaration for financial support
  • Motivation Letter
  • Research proposal outline (MA, PhD)
